text: Ingeborg Vassbakk Løyning (born 13 September 2000) is a Norwegian swimmer. She competed in the women's 100 metre backstroke at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships held in Gwangju, South Korea. Coming from Narvik, she moved to Bærum at age 16 to attend the Norwegian School of Elite Sport. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:People from Narvik Category:Norwegian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Female backstroke swimmers
